2001-xx-xx Jim Garlick <garlick@llnl.gov>

	* : California State University, Chico relinquished copyright.

	* : Added GPL text to all .c files and GPL licence in ./GPL.

	* : Release 1.1

2001-xx-xx Jim Garlick <garlick@llnl.gov>

	* quota.c : quota.fs renamed to quota.conf

	* getconf.[ch] : Renamed from getfs.[ch].

	* getconf.c : Eliminated first field ("code") of quota.conf which 
	was no longer used.

	* quota.c : Use getopt() instead of ad-hoc argv processing.  
	Now it is possible to specify -v and -r at the same time.

	* quota.1, quota.conf.5 : New.

	* : Release 1.0

1998-08-28 Jim Garlick <garlick@llnl.gov>

	* getfs.[ch] : Added field to quota.fs file for percentage, which, 
	if nonzero, causes quota to report when user has exceeded this 
	percentage of hard quota.  Added for benefit of simplitic quotas 
	on NetApp boxes (just implements hard quota; no soft quota, 
	no grace period).

1998-08-27 Jim Garlick <garlick@llnl.gov>

	* quota.c : Changed abbrev() so 1000-1023MB is displayed GB.

	* quota.c : Changed HASBLOCK, HASFILE macros so -1 also indicates 
	!quota (NetApp)

	* : Release 0.2

1998-06-11 Jim Garlick <garlick@llnl.gov>

	* quota.c : Cleanup, port to DEC, Solaris, AIX.

	* quota.c : Added MB / GB / TB abbreviations.

	* quota.c : Added DEC_HACK for ignoring some bad data (see comment 
	in quota.c).

	* : Release 0.1 (first Livermore release)
